# ── OS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# ── Python ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/

# ── Secrets / credentials — NEVER commit ─────────────────────────────────────
# This kit connects to Snowflake via the `snow` CLI, which reads credentials
# from ~/.snowflake/connections.toml on the user's machine — NOT from this repo.
# The patterns below are a safety net so keys/connection files can never be
# committed by accident. (If you ever need to commit a *safe* .toml such as a
# pyproject.toml, force-add it: `git add -f pyproject.toml`.)
*.toml
connection.toml
connections.toml
**/connections.toml
*.p8
*.pem
*.key
*.env
.env*
*credentials*
*secret*

# ── Build / temp ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tmp
*.log
*.pid
output/
dist/
build/

CLAUDE.md
# ── DEMO-path generated SQL (CoCo authors it live; not committed) ─────────────
# The medallion-build / cortex-analyst-search skills write generated Bronze/Silver/
# Gold/semantic SQL into the example's build/ dir for review before running. That
# dir is already covered by the global `build/` rule above; the committed src/*.sql
# stays the golden reference + the 7ptrial path.

# ── Captured external API spec (large, untracked) ─────────────────────────────
openapi.json
